// SPDX-License-Identifier: Apache-2.0 WITH LLVM-exception
//
// test/preprocess/p10/pass.test — P10 expansion order inside
// `#define` body per `docs/spec/nsl_pp.ebnf` notes section + the
// contract topic table in
// `specs/002-m1-lex-preprocess/contracts/preprocessor-seam.contract.md`.
//
// Topic per the table: "%IDENT% splice precedes helper eval inside
// `#define` body".
//
// P10 ordered steps inside a `#define` body:
//   1. `%IDENT%` splices first — look up the inner identifier in the
//      MacroTable and splice the replacement TEXT (not the value).
//   2. Helper calls evaluated left-to-right.
//   3. Operator-precedence reduction per `pp.ebnf §3` precedence
//      table.
//
// Source per tasks.md T046:
//   `#define Y 3`
//   `#define X _int(_pow(%Y%, 2.0))`
//
// Step-by-step expansion at `%X%` use site:
//   step 1 (splice)  : body becomes `_int(_pow(3, 2.0))`
//   step 2 (helpers) : `_pow(3, 2.0)` → 9.0 (real); `_int(9.0)` → 9
//   step 3 (reduce)  : the lone `9` is the final integer value
//
// At the seam the use site emits `tk_decimal_lit 9`.
//
// Tasks.md T046 + FR-017 + spec.md US2 acceptance #3.
//
// **RED state**: the unchanged Phase-3 lexer tokenizes
// `_int(_pow(%Y%,2.0))` literally; the `%Y%` lexes as
// `tk_percent`/`tk_identifier`/`tk_percent`. Phase-4 turns it green.

// RUN: echo '#define Y 3'                       >  %t.nsl
// RUN: echo '#define X _int(_pow(%%Y%%, 2.0))'  >> %t.nsl
// RUN: echo 'reg n = %%X%%;'                    >> %t.nsl
// RUN: %nslc -emit=tokens %t.nsl | FileCheck %s

// CHECK:      tk_reg{{[ \t]+}}reg
// CHECK-NEXT: tk_identifier{{[ \t]+}}n
// CHECK-NEXT: tk_assign{{[ \t]+}}=
// CHECK-NEXT: tk_decimal_lit{{[ \t]+}}9
// CHECK-NEXT: tk_semicolon{{[ \t]+}};
// CHECK-NEXT: tk_eof

// No artifact of the intermediate expansion crosses the seam:
// CHECK-NOT: tk_percent
// CHECK-NOT: tk_dot
// CHECK-NOT: tk_system_function{{[ \t]+}}_int
// CHECK-NOT: tk_system_function{{[ \t]+}}_pow
